From f734ae60b3d28a2370b4c6d729631524c07437f0 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Yakov Till <yakov.till@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 9 Dec 2025 19:48:03 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 13/17] ALSA: hda: aw88399: refactor to use shared library

Create a shared device library for AW88399 that can be used by both
ASoC and HDA drivers, following the established pattern used by
CS35L41 and TAS2781.

This eliminates the cross-subsystem dependency where the HDA driver
was including headers from sound/soc/codecs/ with ugly relative paths:
  #include "../../soc/codecs/aw88399.h"

Now the HDA driver uses the clean include path:
  #include <sound/aw88399.h>

New files:
- include/sound/aw88399.h: Shared header with register definitions
  and device library API
- sound/soc/codecs/aw88399-lib.c: Shared device library with init,
  start, stop, and firmware loading functions

The HDA driver now depends on SND_SOC_AW88399_LIB instead of the
full SND_SOC_AW88399 ASoC driver.

