From 306ca795b8fe72d979b705970efb3341248478e7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Yakov Till <yakov.till@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 14 Dec 2025 19:58:05 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 17/17] ALSA: hda: aw88399: add dither control and stop
 recovery to library

Add missing features to match Nadim's working vendor driver exactly:

1. Dither control:
   - Capture dither_st from DBGCTRL_REG after firmware load
   - Disable dither at start (prevents noise during power-up)
   - Restore dither after unmute if firmware had it enabled

2. Stop recovery:
   - If aw_dev_check_sysint() returns error during stop,
     re-upload DSP firmware via aw88395_dev_fw_update()
   - This recovers from transient DSP errors

These were the only remaining differences between our library
and the working vendor implementation.

Signed-off-by: Yakov Till <yakov.till@gmail.com>
---
 sound/soc/codecs/aw88399-lib.c | 47 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++--
 1 file changed, 45 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/sound/soc/codecs/aw88399-lib.c b/sound/soc/codecs/aw88399-lib.c
index 9753c3d13..70a14fd12 100644
--- a/sound/soc/codecs/aw88399-lib.c
